author: Times Sports Staff
title: BOYS VOLLEYBALL: Sodus blanks Wayne
text:
LYONS — The Lyons girls tennis team had locked up a share of its first Wayne County league title before stepping onto the courts for Wednesday’s season finale. 
East Rochester created a scenario in which the Lions may have to share the spoils. 
The Bombers scored a 3-2 victory over Lyons in the completion of a match suspended Sept. 28. 
Lyons (10-4, 8-2) will share the crown with North Rose-Wolcott if the Cougars down Clyde-Savannah today. If the Golden Eagles spring a surprise, the Lions would own the crown to themselves. 
The doubles tandems of Tori Hoefen and Marissa Nelson, and Kenna Miller and Bethany Seaborn, each won in three sets to key the Bombers (6-6, 5-5). 
Alyssa Wlodarczyk topped No. 1 singles 6-1, 6-2 for the Lions. Morgan Ball won No. 3 singles 6-2, 2-6, 6-4. 
Tuesday 
INDIVIDUAL SECTIONALS 
Class B 
PITTSFORD — Two singles players and a doubles tandem from Palmyra-Macedon reached the semifinal round of the Class B tournament following the early rounds at the Mendon Racquet & Pool Club. 
Third-seeded Erin Graham and fourth-seeded Cara Graham will compete in Friday’s semifinals. In addition, Pal-Mac’s doubles team of Marietta Koeberle and Anna O’Donnell, the top seeds, advanced with 10-1 and 6-2, 7-5 triumphs. 
Penn Yan’s Ashley Owens, the second seed, dropped just four games in two matches en route to a semifinal appearance. Owens will take on Erin Graham in the semis. 
A pair of local doubles tandems are still in contention in the playback portion of the bracket: Penn Yan’s Jenna Curbeau and Shelly Woodard, and Newark’s Ashley Porter and Kathryn Pieters. 
In Class BB, Geneva’s duo of Aidan Camera and Sydne Evans are competing in the playback bracket.
